e Commons. What challenges face you? Who can you turn to? And just how can you make an impact? Crisply written for the non-specialist reader, this fascinating book opens a window onto the perilous world of parliamentary politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLegislatorszGreat BritainvInterviews. 0aLegislatorszGreat Britain. 0aPolitical participationzGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aBrexit.  aBritish politics.  aChange UK.  aHouse of Commons.  aMPs.  acampaigning.  aelections.  agovenrment.  aindependents.  aparliament.  aparliamentary rights.  aparticipation.  aparty splits.  apolitical parties.  apolitics.  asmall parties.1 aThompson, Louise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615302940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526153029423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526153029/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles